\pard\f0\fs28\qc  {\b 34.        Mibora}       Adanson
\par
\pard\f0\fs24\qc  By †T.G. Tutin. 
\par
\par
\pard\f0\fs28 Annuals. Leaves flat. Inflorescence spike-like, unilateral. Spikelets laterally compressed, with 1 floret. Glumes subequal, membranous, longer than the floret, 1-veined, persistent. Lemma 5-veined, truncate, densely hairy, thinner than the glumes. Palea as long as lemma, hairy.
\par
\par
\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. M. minima} (L.) Desv., {\i Obs. Pl. Angers} 45 (1818). Stems 2-15 cm, filiform, tufted. Leaves up to 2(-4) cm, mostly at the base of the plant, glabrous, with an obtuse, cartilaginous apex; sheaths with a wide scarious margin, glabrous, the lower without lamina; ligule up to 1 mm, truncate. Inflorescence 0·5-2 cm, usually purplish, very slender. Spikelets 1·8-3 mm, subsessile, in 2 rows along one side of the rhachis. Glumes oblong to elliptic-oblong, obtuse to slightly emarginate, rounded on the back. Lemma often denticulate at apex. Anthers 1-1·7 mm. 2n = 14.{\i  Sandy and other light soils, damp in winter. S., W. & W.C. Europe, northwards to} c. 53° {\i N. in Wales; an occasional casual elsewhere.} Be Br ?Bu Ga Ge Gr Ho Hs †It Lu.
