\pard\f0\fs28\qc  {\b 35.         Briza}          L.
\par
\pard\f0\fs24\qc  By †T.G. Tutin. 
\par
\par
\pard\f0\fs28 Subglabrous annuals or perennials. Inflorescence usually much branched. Spikelets ovoid or broadly triangular, laterally compressed; florets 4-20. Glumes ovate-orbicular, cordate, 3- to 9-veined, with wide scarious margin. Lemma suborbicular, cordate, 7- to 9-veined, closely imbricate. Palea ovate to obovate, obtuse, shorter than to almost equalling the lemma, with 2 narrowly winged keels. Ovary glabrous; styles terminal. Grain rounded dorsally, flattened ventrally.
