\pard\f0\fs28  {\b 1. B. media} L., {\i Sp. Pl.} 70 (1753). Laxly caespitose perennial 15-100 cm. Stems erect. Leaves 2-7 mm wide, flat, scabridulous on the margin; sheaths smooth; ligule 0·5-1·5 mm. Panicle 4-18 cm, erect, much-branched, lax; lower branches (1-)2 together; pedicels mostly longer than spikelets, very slender. Spikelets 4-7(-12) mm, numerous, pendent, usually purplish; florets 4-12. Glumes 2·5-3·5 mm, concave, cucullate, suborbicular, 3- to 5-veined, subcoriaceous. Lemma c. 4 mm, like the glumes, 7- to 9-veined. Palea somewhat shorter than lemma. 2n = 14, 28.{\i  Grassland. Most of Europe, but only as a casual in the extreme north.} All except Az Bl Cr Fa Is Sb.
