\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 3. B. minor} L.,{\i  Sp. Pl.} 70 (1753). Annual (5-)10-60 cm. Stems erect. Leaves 3-10 mm wide, flat, scabridulous above and on margin; sheaths smooth; ligule 3-6 mm. Panicle 3-20 cm, erect, much-branched, lax; lower branches 1-2 together, patent; pedicels mostly longer than the spikelets, very slender. Spikelets 3-5 mm, numerous, usually pale green; florets 4-8. Glumes 2-3·5 mm, concave, cucullate, suborbicular, 3- to 5-veined, subcoriaceous. Lemma 1·5-2 mm, like the glumes, but papillose on the back, 7- to 9-veined. Palea somewhat shorter than lemma. 2n = 10.{\i  Open habitats. S. & W. Europe, northwards to S. England.} Al Az Bl *Br Co Cr Ga Gr Hs It Ju Lu Sa Si Tu [Be].
