\pard\f0\fs28 More or less caespitose perennials. Leaves flat, plicate or involute; ligule short, truncate or obtuse. Inflorescence spike-like, cylindrical to globose, often bluish, greyish or whitish; bracts at base of inflorescence well-developed. Spikelets laterally compressed, with 2-5 florets. Glumes unequal, membranous, 1- to 3-veined. Lemma 5-veined, membranous, with 2-5 usually aristulate teeth at apex. Palea as long as or longer than lemma.
